NOTICE OF CLAIM OF LIEN
I, Jane P. Whitley, being first duly sworn, depose and say as follows:
Ficial
That I am the Managing Agent of Hidden Valley Association, an Arizona non-profit corporation,
being a Homeowners' Association organized to own, operate and manage the commonly held
facilities of the Association.
2. That the Declaration of Restrictive Covenants For All Phases of Hidden Valley Ranch, A Planned
Area Development, in the City of Prescott, Arizona, According to the Plats Recorded and to be
Recorded in the Office of the yavapai County Recorder, Arizona, recorded November 6, 1979,
as Document #35392, in Book 1257, Pages 565-596, in the official records of Yavapai
County, Arizona, and on November 7, 1979, as Document #35393, in Book 1257, Pages 597-
628, as amended and supplemented ("Declaration"), is a covenant running with and binding the
land in said subdivision; that said Declaration imposes annual assessments on individual parcels
of property within said subdivision and creates a lien of assessment in order to collect
delinquent assessments; the assessment is both a lien against the real property and the
personal obligation of the owner of record or the purchaser of said real property.
opy
3. That the owner of record is FOUNDERS DEVELOPMENT, L.L.C ., an Arizona limited liability
company, whose real property is located at 1739 Kaibab Loop, in the City of Prescott, County7
of Yavapai, State of Arizona; Lot P-39, of HIDDEN VALLEY RANCH PHASE IV, according
to the plat of record in the office of the County Recorder of yavapai County, Arizona,
recorded in Book 21 of Maps, Page 84.
4. That the assessment on said real property is delinquent in the amount of $872.00, being due
and presently unpaid.
Said assessment due creates a continuing lien on the above described real property and
continues to accrue, plus interest, late charges, lien fees and additional charges approved by
the Board of Directors of the Hidden Valley Association.
That this Notice and Claim of Lien is recorded to perfect the lien assessment created by said
Declaration, and one copy hereof has been delivered to the County Recorder of Yavapai County,
Arizona to be filed and recorded and one copy delivered to said owner/purchaser by certified
mail, return receipt requested.
